race.description: Ladbrokes Racing Extras In Multi Handicap (58)
race.comment: SKY BLUE (9) finished out of the money two starts back then she settled well back and was beaten 2.5 lengths when eighth in a 1100m contest at Ipswich eight days ago. Kelsey Lenton gets the best out of this four-year-old mare. Finds the right race this time and can find winning form. KENTUCKY ROSE (6) was prominent at the turn and finished third last start over 800m at Kilcoy, beaten 1.4 lengths. Will be rock-hard fit. Suitably placed so anticipating another forward showing. ARTOPIA (8) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on from the favourable draw. RUNAROUND SUE (7) has won over this course and distance and looks a must for the multiples.
